   "source": [
    "## 1. INTRODUCTION\n",
    "\n",
    "### 1.1 Project Overview\n",
    "\n",
    "This project implements a **machine learning classification model** using the **K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN)** algorithm to classify iris flowers into three species based on their physical measurements. This is a fundamental project in machine learning that demonstrates core concepts including data preprocessing, exploratory data analysis, model training, and evaluation.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 1.2 Objective\n",
    "\n",
    "The primary objectives of this project are:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Load and explore** the Iris dataset\n",
    "2. **Perform Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)** to understand the data\n",
    "3. **Preprocess the data** through feature selection and train-test splitting\n",
    "4. **Build a KNN classification model** to predict iris species\n",
    "5. **Evaluate model performance** using accuracy, confusion matrix, and classification report\n",
    "6. **Make predictions** on new flower samples\n",
    "\n",
    "### 1.3 Dataset Description\n",
    "\n",
    "The **Iris Dataset** is one of the most famous datasets in machine learning and statistics. It was introduced by Ronald Fisher in 1936 and contains measurements of iris flowers from three different species.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Dataset Statistics:**\n",
    "- **Total Samples:** 150 flowers\n",
    "- **Number of Features:** 4 measurements\n",
    "- **Number of Classes:** 3 iris species\n",
    "- **Samples per Class:** 50 flowers of each species (balanced dataset)\n",
    "\n",
    "### 1.4 Features and Target Variable\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Input Features (X):\n",
    "1. **Sepal Length (cm):** Length of the sepal (outer leaf-like structure)\n",
    "2. **Sepal Width (cm):** Width of the sepal\n",
    "3. **Petal Length (cm):** Length of the petal (flower leaf)\n",
    "4. **Petal Width (cm):** Width of the petal\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Target Variable (y):\n",
    "The **species** of iris flower with three possible values:\n",
    "- **Setosa** - Small species with narrow petals\n",
    "- **Versicolor** - Medium-sized species with medium petals\n",
    "- **Virginica** - Large species with wide petals\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
